Copyprotection certain gamepublishers use. Can fuck up your PC worse than you can imagine. Despite what the makers brag, it is incredibly simple to bypass. Disable your IDE optical drive and mount the DVD/CD in a virtual SCSI drive and it will work flawlessly. 

Star-force, makers of Starforce protection, is a russian company who has employees that once were active virus-writers and crackers themselves. They vandalize and whitewash the wikipedia page on starforce constantly and harass sites that post negative stories about their malware.

UBIsoft and CDV recently dropped Starforce from their games because of the negative experience with it. Users with legitimate copies have their games unable to run, systems reboot at odd times and their optical drives are slowed down to a crawl.
